Shadow<br>
 <!--129-->The Witch-king, Lord of Angmar x2<br>
 Úlairë Enquëa, Lieutenant og Morgul x2<br>
 Úlairë Cantëa, Lieutenant of Dol Goldur x3<br>
 Úlairë Nelya, Ringwraith in Twilight x3<br>
 Úlairë Toldëa, Messenger of Morgul x2<br>
 Úlairë Attëa, Keeper of Dol Goldur x2<br>
 Isengard Warrior x4<br>
 <!--113-->Nazgul Sword x4<br>
 <!--107-->Drawn to Its Power x4<br>
 News of Mordor x4    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Free peoples<br>
 Bid 3 (or 2 if you are meeting Nazgul). If you win the bid, you should start. But going second is not a problem, as your Nazgul will gain benefit from their sites. <br>
<br>
This deck is not designed to win skirmishes and to kill as many minions as possible, its goal is to prevent and heal wounds, thus keeping the fellowship alive.<br>
<br>
Do not be afraid to sacrifice companions when you must, as the only important companions in this deck are Gandalf and Frodo. Even if you are playing against Uruks or Nazgul. Intimidate helps out alot against Enquea. <br>
<br>
This deck does not have any condition removal, I did not fear any of them enough to put in Sleep Caradras.<br>
<br>
Shadow<br>
 The goal with the shadow side is having one or two news of Mordor on my hand, so that you can kill of key companions. When you kill them, you will (hopefully) add burdens so that the Nazgul Swords, Toldeas, and Enquas will be very deadly. I chose the Isengard Warriors because they have  two very nice abilities, and because they hopefully will not die before you have used news of Mordor.<br>
 <br>
I just didnt have any space for Morgul Gates, blade tip and Black Breath. Blade tip does not work well with Drawn to Its Power either, as it is not the Nazgul that kills the companion.<br>
<br>
You should usually walk trough the sites like this: <br>
1-2, 2-3, 3-4, 4-6, 6-8, 8-9.<br>
<br>
I know that this deck is not perfect, but I wanted to try something new. I was tired of all the Archery/Uruk or Archery/Nazgul-Breath/tip decks in my area. <br>
<br>
Sorry for my bad English. (I&#39;m from Norway)<br>
